<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="60" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,152,874]" pageId="3" pageNumber="60">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,331,693,719]" pageId="3" pageNumber="60">Etymology</emphasis>
. The name for this species is obviously for the island of Leyte, in the southeast of the 
<collectingCountry box="[151,272,732,758]" name="Philippines" pageId="3" pageNumber="60">Philippine</collectingCountry>
archipelago.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="60" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,152,874]" pageId="3" pageNumber="60">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,312,770,796]" pageId="3" pageNumber="60">Remarks</emphasis>
. This new species can immediately be separated from the generic type-species 
<taxonomicName box="[1251,1436,770,795]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Lumawigia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="60" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gibbicephala">
<emphasis box="[1251,1436,770,795]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="60">L. gibbicephala</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by being smaller (length: ca. 
<number box="[528,567,809,835]" pageId="3" pageNumber="60" value="9.5">9.5</number>
–11.0 mm), bronze, green to blue-green and is from Leyte, while 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Lumawigia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="60" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gibbicephala">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="60">L. gibbicephala</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is larger (length: 14.0 mm), purple and is from northern Luzon.
</paragraph>
